\section{Building the Lean: Step by Step}\label{sec:recipe}
% ============================================================

You are pricing bond $Y$ at time $t$. This is the procedure.

\subsection{Step 1: Choose the Lean Space}

\begin{verbatim}
  if CDS_liquid(issuer):     lean_space = hazard_rate
  elif Y.is_callable:        lean_space = OAS
  else:                       lean_space = z_spread
\end{verbatim}

All subsequent operations happen in this space.

\subsection{Step 2: Gather and Clean Same-Bond Sources}

For each direct observation of $Y$ (TRACE prints, composite quotes, own RFQ history):

\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=2em]
  \item Convert the raw observation (price) to spread using $Y$'s analytics and the current benchmark curve.
  \item Apply source-specific corrections (side/half-spread, flow pressure, capped size, de-lagging).
  \item Assign a reliability weight (age decay $\times$ size weight $\times$ source base weight).
\end{enumerate}

The output is a set of cleaned mid-spread estimates with weights: $\{(\hat{s}_k, w_k)\}_{\text{same-bond}}$.

\subsection{Step 3: Gather and Clean Cross-Instrument Sources}

For each indirect source (CDS, related bonds, ETFs):

\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=2em]
  \item Obtain the source instrument's current spread (from its own lean or live data).
  \item Apply the conversion model to estimate $Y$'s spread (basis model for CDS, structured conversion for related bonds, beta/DV01 mapping for ETFs).
  \item Compute the regime-conditional conversion uncertainty $\sigma_{\text{conv}}(t)$.
  \item Assign a reliability weight that decreases as conversion uncertainty increases.
\end{enumerate}

The output is a set of converted spread estimates with weights: $\{(\hat{s}_k, w_k)\}_{\text{cross-instr}}$.

\subsection{Step 4: Aggregate in Spread Space}

\begin{enumerate}[leftmargin=2em]
  \item Combine all sources: $\{(\hat{s}_k, w_k)\} = \text{same-bond} \cup \text{cross-instr}$.
  \item Enforce the cross-instrument weight cap: if cross-instrument weight exceeds $\theta_{\text{cross,max}}(r_t)$ of total, rescale down.
  \item Compute the lean mid-spread:
  \begin{equation}
  s_{\text{lean}} = \frac{\sum_k w_k \cdot \hat{s}_k}{\sum_k w_k}
  \end{equation}
  \item Compute source disagreement:
  \begin{equation}
  \sigma_{\text{lean}} = \sqrt{\frac{\sum_k w_k (\hat{s}_k - s_{\text{lean}})^2}{\sum_k w_k}}
  \end{equation}
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Step 5: Build the Lean Bid/Offer in Spread Space}

Using the regime-specific half-spread model for bond $Y$ at the target trade size:

\begin{align}
s_{\text{lean}}^{\text{bid}} &= s_{\text{lean}} + \hat{h}_{\mathcal{R}(Y)}(\text{size}) + \psi \cdot \sigma_{\text{lean}} \\
s_{\text{lean}}^{\text{offer}} &= s_{\text{lean}} - \hat{h}_{\mathcal{R}(Y)}(\text{size}) - \psi \cdot \sigma_{\text{lean}}
\end{align}

In spread space: bid = wider spread = lower price. The $\psi \cdot \sigma_{\text{lean}}$ term widens the spread when sources disagree.

\subsection{Step 6: Convert to Price}

This is the \textbf{only} place bond-specific analytics are applied:

\begin{align}
P_{\text{lean}}^{\text{bid}} &= \text{PriceFromSpread}(s_{\text{lean}}^{\text{bid}},\; Y,\; \text{curve}(t),\; \text{vol}(t)) \\
P_{\text{lean}}^{\text{offer}} &= \text{PriceFromSpread}(s_{\text{lean}}^{\text{offer}},\; Y,\; \text{curve}(t),\; \text{vol}(t))
\end{align}

The full bond pricer handles coupon schedule, maturity, call schedule, day count, accrued interest, convexity --- all of it.

\subsection{Step 7: Assign Confidence}

\begin{equation}
\text{confidence} = \underbrace{\min\!\left(1,\; \frac{\sum w_k}{w_{\text{suff}}}\right)}_{\text{data sufficiency}} \times \underbrace{(1 - P(\text{stress}) \cdot \delta)}_{\text{regime penalty}} \times \underbrace{\max\!\left(0,\; 1 - \frac{\sigma_{\text{lean}}}{\sigma_{\text{max}}}\right)}_{\text{source agreement}}
\end{equation}

Downstream behavior:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{@{}ll@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Confidence} & \textbf{Action} \\
\midrule
$> 0.7$ & Quote normally off the lean \\
$0.4$--$0.7$ & Widen spreads proportionally \\
$0.2$--$0.4$ & Quote very wide, or only favorable-direction RFQs \\
$< 0.2$ & Decline the RFQ \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\subsection{Step 8: Output}

The lean for bond $Y$ at time $t$:

\begin{verbatim}
  LeanOutput:
      cusip, timestamp, lean_space
      spread: mid, bid, offer              (bps)
      price:  mid, bid, offer              (clean $)
      confidence                            (0 to 1)
      sigma_lean                            (source disagreement, bps)
      dominant_source                       (highest-weight source)
      n_sources, total_weight
      cross_instr_fraction                  (% weight from cross-instr)
      regime                                (calm / stressed)
      liquidity_regime                      (bond's cluster)
      source_details[]                      (per-source audit trail)
\end{verbatim}

This output feeds the quoting engine, which adds the inventory lean and alpha signal on top.


